The article is a transcript of remarks made by Secretary-General Guterres and President Trump at the United Nations Headquarters in New York. Secretary-General Guterres highlights the inspiration and privilege of working in New York, as well as the shared values between the United Nations Charter and the United States Constitution. He also mentions the upcoming 75th anniversary of the United Nations and the 50th anniversary of the moon landing, emphasizing the need to work together to solve global problems. President Trump praises the potential of the United Nations to promote peace and acknowledges the progress made in their discussions on world events. He also expresses gratitude for the presence of the attendees and congratulates Secretary-General Guterres on his work.